        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 5:21PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
RDU International, or 7 miles north of Cary, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pilot, Youngsville, Zebulon, Research Triangle, Wake Forest, Falls
Lake, Knightdale, Emit, Wendell, and Falls Lake Boat Ramp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
